Week 2 (October 2025)

Topics Covered:
Advanced Microsoft Excel: Pivot Tables, Pivot Charts, Conditional Formatting, VLOOKUP/XLOOKUP, IF, COUNTIF, SUMIFS, data cleaning using Power Query.

Breakthroughs:
Built dynamic dashboards using Pivot Tables.
Learned to automate repetitive cleaning tasks using Power Query.
Understood how lookup functions can link multiple datasets efficiently.

Challenges:
Struggled with nested formulas initially—resolved by breaking logic into smaller parts and testing step-by-step.

Next Steps:
Apply Excel automation techniques on real business datasets (sales, profit, customer segmentation).

Reflection:
Excel is not “basic” — it’s a powerful analytical tool when used with advanced formulas and Power Query.
